A question about use your pattern in a context ApplicationContext. I explain.

static class Program {  
[STAThread]  
static void Main(){  
Application.EnableVisualStyles();  
Application.SetCompatibleTextRenderingDefault(false);  
Task<appcontext> actx = AppContext.CreateAsync();  
Application.Run(actx); // THIS FAILS  
}}

class AppContext : ApplicationContext  
{...}

In AppContext I implemented the Factory Pattern but when I try to pass the actx instance to the Application.Run() method compiler fails with the error

Error CS1503: Argument #1 cannot convert 'System.Threading.Tasks.Task<appcontext>' expression to type 'System.Windows.Forms.Form'

The problem is that I can pass AppContext but not Task<appcontext>.  
What workaround can I use?  
Nicola

